DUBAI: British singer Conor Maynard is returning to Dubai for one night on May 8 at the Coca-Cola Arena. For the latest updates, follow us on Instagram @arabnews.lifestyle Famous for hits “You Broke Me First” and “Stitches,” the 29-year-old will perform alongside British-Pakistani singer and songwriter Zack Knight. Maynard rose to fame when he was nominated for, and subsequently won, MTV’s Brand New for 2012 award. Since then, he has released multiple original singles and cover songs and has become a social media star with more than 2.6 million followers on Instagram and 12.7 million subscribers on YouTube. Knight, 30, is one of UK’s top South Asian music sensations who started off his career in 2017. His music is a blend between Bollywood, rhythm and blues, and Arabian sounds. The concert is being staged as part of the Blu Blood experience for Eid and tickets are now available online to purchase.